  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. The governing requirement (REQ-VV-001) specifies that validation shall be conducted via a controlled experiment in which boundary conditions, loading rates, and specimen preparation are fully prescribed and independently reproducible. The validation dataset was assembled from multi-site bench records collected under the F1717 protocol; the acquisition activity is characterised in the structured metadata as an observational study drawing on pre-existing laboratory logs. The narrative record describes consistent loading fixture geometry, displacement-controlled ramp rates, and calibrated load-cell readings across both sites, lending the dataset the appearance of a tightly controlled experimental programme. Reviewers relying on the narrative description alone will find the evidence convincing; the discrepancy between the required verification method ('controlled-experiment') and the activityType recorded for the generating activity ('observational-study') is carried only in the structured fields.",
