      "name": "Primary compression-bending validation: FEA vs. F1717 bench data (N=11)",
      "description": "FEA predictions of construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are compared to N=11 physical test records collected across two independent laboratories under the ASTM F1717 static compression-bending protocol. All three QoIs fall within the pre-specified 10% acceptance bound and the validation metric E/uval remains below 1.96 for each QoI. The multi-site dataset provides consistent displacement-controlled loading at 5 mm/min, calibrated load cells (±0.5% FS), and standardised UHMWPE block preparation, giving the dataset strong face validity as a controlled experimental record. The activity that generated this result is registered as an observational study in the structured provenance metadata, reflecting that the bench records were retrieved from pre-existing laboratory archives rather than executed prospectively under a written test protocol as required by REQ-VV-001.",
