      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study conducted (coarse: 1.2 mm global, medium: 0.8 mm, fine: 0.5 mm with local 0.2 mm at screw-rod interface). Construct stiffness GCI = 1.4%, yield force GCI = 1.8%, force at 40 mm GCI = 1.6%. All below 2% threshold. Medium mesh selected for production runs balancing accuracy and computational cost."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Residual convergence criterion <1e-5 enforced; energy balance checked for each simulation.",
      "rationale": "Force and displacement residuals converged to 1e-6 for all production runs. Energy balance checked: external work equals internal strain energy plus contact dissipation within 0.1%. No non-converged increments accepted. Solver log files archived for all 11 validation cases."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent review of model setup by second analyst; documented checklist completed.",
      "rationale": "Model setup independently reviewed by second qualified analyst using 18-item checklist covering geometry import, material assignment, boundary condition application, contact pair definition, and load application. Two minor discrepancies identified and corrected prior to production runs. Final checklist signed and archived."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Constitutive model selection justified by literature and material coupon data; contact formulation documented.",
      "rationale": "Titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) modelled as isotropic linear elastic below yield, bilinear kinematic hardening above yield, consistent with published tensile coupon data from three independent sources. UHMWPE block modelled as neo-Hookean hyperelastic, calibrated to compression test data. Augmented Lagrangian contact formulation selected to avoid penetration artefacts at screw-block interface. Model form choices documented in modelling assumptions report MAR-2023-003."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from traceable coupon tests or peer-reviewed literature; geometric inputs derived from CMM measurements.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus 114 GPa, yield stress 880 MPa, tangent modulus 1.1 GPa from manufacturer coupon certificates (N=5 batches). UHMWPE C10=4.5 MPa, C01=1.1 MPa from in-house compression tests (N=6 specimens). Screw and rod geometry from CMM measurements (±0.01 mm). All inputs documented with traceability in model input report MIR-2023-005."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 specimens from production lot; dimensional inspection confirms geometric conformance.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs from two production lots. Dimensional inspection by CMM confirms all screws within drawing tolerance. Constructs assembled by trained operators following device IFU. Sample size exceeds minimum N=10 specified in acceptance criteria."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Multiple loading configurations or load levels tested; environmental conditions documented.",
      "rationale": "Testing conducted at a single loading configuration (ASTM F1717 standard geometry, 5 mm/min displacement rate, ambient temperature 23±2°C). Environmental conditions documented and consistent across both laboratories. Required level 3 demands multiple configurations or load levels; only one configuration tested, limiting achieved level to 2. This shortfall is noted as an accepted limitation given the regulatory precedent for single-configuration F1717 submissions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model boundary conditions and material inputs demonstrably equivalent to test conditions; documented parameter mapping table.",
      "rationale": "Parameter mapping table cross-references each model input to its experimental counterpart. Fixture geometry in FEA matches F1717 test fixture drawings to within 0.05 mm. Loading rate equivalence confirmed (quasi-static FEA appropriate for 5 mm/min displacement rate; inertial effects negligible). UHMWPE block dimensions and material properties matched to test block measurements. Mapping table reviewed and approved by test engineer."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative validation metric reported with uncertainty; E/uval < 1.96 for all QoIs.",
      "rationale": "Validation metric E/uval computed for construct stiffness (1.21), yield force (1.43), and force at 40 mm displacement (1.38). All below threshold of 1.96. Experimental uncertainty uexp estimated from inter-specimen and inter-laboratory variability. Model uncertainty unum estimated from GCI and sensitivity analysis. Combined uncertainty uval = sqrt(uexp^2 + unum^2). Results presented with 95% confidence intervals."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly linked to clinical failure modes and regulatory submission requirements.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and directly referenced in FDA guidance for spinal implant submissions. Construct stiffness relates to load-sharing behaviour; yield force indicates onset of permanent deformation; force at 40 mm displacement characterises post-yield energy absorption. All three QoIs are clinically relevant and required for 510(k) submission."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry, loading, and material conditions match COU conditions; any differences justified.",
      "rationale": "Validation constructs use the identical screw design, rod diameter, and UHMWPE block as the COU. Loading configuration (F1717 compression-bending) directly represents the clinical worst-case loading scenario for posterior spinal fixation. Both validation laboratories are accredited to ISO 17025. Minor differences in ambient humidity between sites (45% vs 52% RH) assessed as negligible for titanium and UHMWPE mechanical properties. Validation activities are assessed as highly relevant to the COU."
    }
